public class DefaultConstraintEditor
extends ConstraintEditor

An editor for specifying generic constraints in refinements. Constraints are attached to self (the refinement) or to a child.

The editor is implemented as a frame using JList objects, a JCheckBox and JButtons.

The editor can be created with no arguments or with a given refinement which will be set as the current refinement whose conditions and effects are to be specified. Subsequently, the refinement in the editor can be set using the setRefinement method.

DefaultConstraintEditor

public DefaultConstraintEditor(java.awt.Frame owner)
Creates an editor for specifying time point relations. The editor has components for selecting two time points of two sub-activities, and two buttons (Ok, Cancel) "- enter pattern-value statements,", "- select whether you are specifying a condition or an effect,", "- select the node to which the condition/effect applies."});
